<br>
1) The twist. <br>
<br>
I was either two lazy, or stubborn to twist in place to make sure the server knew i wasn't moving while casting, even though I knew about it. <br>
<br>
I almost never get interrupts now while kiting.<br>
<br>
<br>
2) Checking for a *successful* hide and THEN medding during rotting<br>
<br>
While rotting, I had been trying to med to increase mana and reduce downtime, but kept picking up aggro from wanderers.<br>
<br>
At first I tried hiding, then /book but it didn't help.<br>
<br>
The single most important change I have made is to:<br>
<br>
Root Mob<br>
Do Whatever -- DoT, etc.<br>
<br>
Click Hide, and then con mob, if mob doesn't con indiff, turn off hide and repeat until he does, then...<br>
Med<br>
<br>
I attrack no wanderers except those that see through hide this way, and when the root holds exceptionally long, can recover quite a bit of mana, secure in my knowledge that I won't get ganked.<br>
<br>
At level 35, I will be able to use F9 to watch for wanderers, but this system works great at level 27.<br>
<br>
Just wanted to share, as I am pretty excited at how much eaiser these changes have made my soloing.<br>
<br>
