That’s great you learned some of these tactics early on in your Druid Career. Couple other things you might find Useful.  One is what I call the No Look Curve Dish. This applies to when you are Quad Kiting. I also have what’s called the No Look While Looking Target Acquisition. <br>
<br>
The No Look Curve Dish is when you have ensnared a group of MOBs to quad kite, or what every number to kite.  You run, pivot left or right, than stop, rotate either left or right and cast while pivoting/rotating.  As long as you are set in a fixed point, rotation is not registered to the Sever as actual Movement. You can pivot with zero interrupts.<br>
<br>
No Look While Looking Target Acquisition is a little more Tricky.  Target a MOB, have that MOB in your target area highlighted, check the area for your 2nd MOB. Once you see your 2nd MOB Ensnare your 1st Target, you don’t have to be looking at the MOB to ensnare him. Once you cast Ensnare hit the Ecs Key and grab the next MOB. Why the Esc Key, because in some zones, like the Move Stop Server Translation, it can be slow.<br>
<br>
