<br>
You will notice that when you are kiting that when you stop to cast and unless you stand still for 3 seconds you will get an spell interrupt.<br>
<br>
So what a lot of us did/do, was obviously count out for 3 seconds after stopping before starting to cast.  (3 Count).<br>
<br>
But, if you turn immediately after stopping, for turning never interrupts a spell, you could cast immediately.<br>
<br>
Some players will do a quick, sit and stand, does the same thing, but more inconvenient for me at least...<br>
<br>
Now, I never got it to work with mouselook(twist), but if you turn immediately after stopping with you keyboard button, you can even cast the spell while you are turning.<br>
<br>
